PLEASE CONSULT CURRENT UCSD GENERAL CATALOG FOR ANY ADDITIONAL </strong></p><p><strong>INFORMATION. </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>Effective Fall 2017, major preparation will be required for this major. For details, visit: </strong><a href=\"http://admissions.ucsd.edu/MajorPrep\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>http://admissions.ucsd.edu/MajorPrep</strong></a></p><p><br></p><p>Students must apply to be directly admitted to the Structural Engineering major. Transfer students must have completed the</p><p>following courses in order to be considered for admission to the Structural Engineering major.</p><p><br></p><p>• Calculus I-for Science and Engineering (Math. 20A)</p><p>• Calculus II-for Science and Engineering (Math. 20B)</p><p>• Calculus and Analytic Geometry (Math. 20C)</p><p>• Differential Equations (Math. 20D)</p><p>• Linear Algebra (Math. 18)</p><p>• Complete calculus-based physics series with lab experience (Physics 2A-B-C)</p><p>• Chemistry 6A </p><p><br></p><p>For more details regarding transfer admission, please visit the Undergraduate Admission page on our website; <a href=\"https://se.ucsd.edu/academics/undergraduate-program/undergraduate-admission\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://se.ucsd.edu/academics/undergraduate-program/undergraduate-admission</a></p><p><br></p><p>Effective Summer 2024, the Structural Engineering major will no longer be considered a selective/capped major. Students who are not directly admitted into the major can switch into the major by using the Major/Minor Tool on TritonLink. </p><p><br></p><p>Courses that have not been articulated and do not show an equivalent transfer course on <a href=\"http://assist.org/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">ASSIST.ORG</a> must be approved via petition on an individual basis by the SE department. </p><p><br></p><p><strong>Special Advising Note: </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>The following courses are recommended preparation for all transfer students considering admission to the Structural </strong></p><p><strong>Engineering major. Preparing well for the major helps students move efficiently toward graduation. </strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong> • Matlab based algorithms and programming for structural engineering or equivalent </strong></p><p><strong> • Statics or equivalent</strong></p><p><br></p><p>While structural engineering is often viewed as a sub-discipline of civil engineering, we take a cross-disciplinary approach to</p><p>structural engineering at UCSD by developing an undergraduate curriculum, fully accredited by ABET (Accreditation Board for</p><p>Engineering Technology), as well as a full graduate program, emphasizing structural design of not only civil engineering structures,</p><p>(such as buildings, bridge, and earth dams) but also aerospace structures, mechanical structures, offshore, and marine structures. A</p><p>cross-disciplinary education allows our graduates to find employment in any of the above mentioned engineering disciplines, which</p><p>provides the student with great flexibility in employment after graduating with a B.S. in structural engineering. For more information</p><p>please visit <a href=\"https://se.ucsd.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://se.ucsd.edu</a></p>","groupId":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","position":0,"area":"General"},{"type":"GeneralText","content":"<p>UC San Diego Advanced Placement (AP) and International Baccalaureate (IB) credit policies are detailed in the links below:</p><p><br></p><p>Advanced Placement (AP) <a href=\"https://www.ucsd.edu/catalog/pdf/APC-chart.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.ucsd.edu/catalog/pdf/APC-chart.pdf</a></p><p><br></p><p>International Baccalaureate (IB) <a href=\"https://catalog.ucsd.edu/_files/international-baccalaureate-credits-chart.pdf\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">https://catalog.ucsd.edu/_files/international-baccalaureate-credits-chart.pdf</a></p>","groupId":"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000","position":1,"area":"General"}]
